==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Choke pear
<hw>Choke" pear`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of pear that
has a rough, astringent taste, and is swallowed with difficulty, or
which contracts the mucous membrane of the mouth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sarcasm by which one is put to silence; anything
that can not be answered.</def> <mark>[Low]</mark> <rj><au>S.
Richardson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Choker</ent>⟦br⟧
